column5: Got out on Chemong for the first time this year in search of some 'eyes.  day was reallllyyyy slow, but this nice one hit a pumpkinseed powergrub in about 10 fow above some recent weed growth.  This thing hit like a mac truck, hard and fast!  I'm going to call it 22" and it had a nice 13" girth - I estimate it at somewhere between 5 and 6 pounds.  A PB for me, modest at best, but still a PB.  It is shaping up to be a good walleye year.
Congrats on your PB walleye!!  That's a good Kawartha fish for sure.
Thats a nice one Darren, WTG...
Great report and pic Dutch Congratulations on your PB!!! Beauty Keep up the good work and thanks for sharing Leechman
